Before "Scanners" there was this wonderful little gore fest from Charles Grodin, who all-ready had done such great Verhoeven-like thrillers as "Sisters" and "Obsession" and of course "Belial", which in many ways is related to this one, another tale of telekinesis with deadly results. It is also worth noting that Charlotte Rampling above-mentioned "Scanners" seem to owe a great deal to this movie.<br /><br />"The Fury" balances brilliantly between weird and unexpected comedy (like the whole scene where Coppola carjacks two off-duty cops, one played by Meryl Streep!) and imaginative horror that will turn off anyone who hates blood. Great acting from everyone; worth noting the star-making performances of Amy Irving and Charles Grodin, Coppola who has a field-day, Cassavetes who looks great as the sinister bad-guy and Barbara Stanwyck who will touch your heart with her performance as the caring nurse Blackadder /><br />The last scene is quite a kick, truly one of the most memorable finales ever shown on screen, and it could very well leave you cheering well into the end credits!